title: H.S. gymnastics: Passaic County championships preview - Girls Gymnastics
text:
Passaic County gymnastics championships preview 
WHEN: Today, 5 p.m.
WHERE: West Milford
TEAMS (In order of high score): Wayne Valley, Wayne Hills, West Milford, Clifton, Passaic Valley
RETURNING TOP THREE: Nicole Sanzari, Wayne Hills (first, bars; third, beam); Linnea Huber, West Milford (first, beam; second, floor; third, vault); Alexa O'Hanna, Wayne Valley (first, floor); Samantha Wong, Clifton (third, bars); Anna Badami, Wayne Hills (third, floor)
TOP ALL-AROUNDS (season best): Rachael Bussanich, Wayne Valley (37.05); Tonia Golam, Wayne Valley (34.325); Huber (34.3); Sanzari (34.225); Kristen Wong, Clifton (33.0); Samantha Wong (32.25); Maggie Coyle, West Milford (32.1)
OUTLOOK: Wayne Valley is the only team in the field to score triple digits this year, which makes it the favorite to claim a second title in four seasons. The 2014 all-around champ, Alyssa Blake of Wayne Hills, is injured and will not compete.
